main event: An unidentified flying object was reported in Miami, Florida on March 6, 1962, observed through binoculars and a camera.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 10 minutes and involved one object moving from west to east,The sky was hazy with 3/10 cloud cover during the sighting,The object was described as having lights that resembled photonizing stars,The observer used binoculars and mentioned observing strong skies in the Ursa Major constellation,Two photographs were reported to be taken during the observation.
witness description: An amateur astronomer who followed up with reports and photographs while working on an astronomy project.
